[{'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'Medecins Sans Frontieres-Operational Center Amsterdam/Artsen Zonder Grenzen Nederland', 'logo': None, 'url': None, 'employees': {'start': None, 'end': None}}, 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2023}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'profile_positions': [{'location': 'Amsterdam, North Holland, Netherlands', 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2023}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'company': 'Medecins Sans Frontieres-Operational Center Amsterdam/Artsen Zonder Grenzen Nederland', 'description': "- To lead, provide direction, and coordinate the activities of the Logistics department and ensure efficiency, transparency and accountability.
- To formulate the short and long term vision, goals and strategies with regard to supply chain management and logistics and technical support.
- To ensure pertinence and reinforce the effectiveness of the supply chain, logistical services and technical support capabilities, to facilitate the implementation of the Operational (medical humanitarian) ambitions outlined in the OCA Strategic Plan (SP).
- To provide strong leadership dedicated to fostering a cohesive and collaborative working environment underpinned by MSF’s mission and values.
Accountable for the delivery of relevant and effective supply chain and logistical/technical support services to the OCA medical humanitarian operations and for the assigned departmental resources.
- Oversees the Logistics department’s strategic direction and ensures alignment with the overall strategic framework of OCA.
- Formulates vision, goals and strategies and ensures effective strategic guidance, policies and processes, standards and guidelines are in place to support effective implementation.
- Formulates and ensures implementation of the Logistics department’s Functional Strategy in line with the Strategic Plan and MSF's overarching goals and strategies.
- Drives transformation and change by effectively communicating vision and rationale for change, supporting animated engagement, and ensuring inclusive processes.
- Develops strategic, tactical and operational collaboration with regard to the supply chain and logistics and technical support services and activities with other MSF sections, with a view of enhancing synergies, efficient decision-making and effective, high quality service provision.", 'title': 'Director of Supply & Logistics', 'employment_type': 'Full-time'}]}, {'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'MSF-Operational Center Amsterdam/Artsen Zonder Grenzen Nederland', 'logo': None, 'url': None, 'employees': {'start': None, 'end': None}}, 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}, 'end': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2023}}, 'profile_positions': [{'location': 'Amsterdam, The Netherlands', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}, 'end': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2023}}, 'company': 'MSF-Operational Center Amsterdam/Artsen Zonder Grenzen Nederland', 'description': 'Contributes to the development, supports and facilitates the implementation of, the OCA Logistics Functional Strategy and provides input to operational and medical strategies concerning OCA logistics support.
Provides leadership and direction regarding development, support and implementation of operational logistics policies, guidelines, tools and training and ensures implementation of an effective and efficient support model in regards to OCA operational logistics and field supply.
Oversees and drives transformation and continuous improvement ensuring effective and efficient field logistics support and service levels.
Actively participates in the Logistics department leadership team and organises cross-functional/ organisational collaborative interaction within and among teams involved with logistics and field supply chain management. Ensure connectedness and pro-active follow-up with regard to transversal issues.
Oversees, analyses and monitors the implementation of operational logistics policies and procedures, and the integrity, impact and quality of operational logistics support to our medical humanitarian projects;
Defines and ensures implementation of an effective and efficient Logistics-Supply support model for OCA in regards to operational logistics/supply;
Provides leadership regarding development and support to implementation of Operation Logistics policies, guidelines, tools and training contents;
Collaborates with the OCA Human Resources department with regard to defining and validating field logistical job profiles and maintaining an adequate (deputy) LogCo pool.
